Defendant in custody.
The Court sentences the defendant to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of five and one-half (5.5) years.  That is two (2) years initial confinement followed by three and one-half (3.5) years extended supervision. 
The defendant is not eligible for the prison programs.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1)	Pay court costs;
2)	pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3)	maintain absolute sobriety;
4)	assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the department's assessment process;
5)	AODA assessment and follow through;
6)	Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
7)	Maintain fulltime employment, schooling, work search or combination
The defendant has credit for 203 days.
Minutes.

Defendant in custody on WRIT.
The State moves to delete the repeater enhancer on count 2.  Motion granted.
NO CONTEST plea entered to the amended charge in count 2, injury by intoxicated use of vehicle.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in counts 1, 3 and 4; 1st degree reckless injury as repeater, injury by prohibited BAC and hit and run with injury.  Motion granted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for five (5) years, consecutive to the prison sentence presently being served to commence upon defendants completion of extended supervision.
Conditions of probation:
1) Pay court costs;
2) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3) provide DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
4) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
5) maintain fulltime employment, schooling or job search;
6) maintain absolute sobriety;
7) no contact with bars or liquor stores;
8) pay restitution  TBD.  The restitution matter will be held open for two weeks.  Parties will request a hearing if necessary.
In addition, the Court orders a two (2) year license revocation.
